snippet.textDisplay: Cargo space may be a deciding factor in purchasing a car. Advertised cargo capacity may be 68 ft³ for the Y and for the Model 3 it is 15 ft³. Of course a blanket might be used as well to cover an oversize diamond... I am not aware of other vehicles with similar outside dimensions that provide nearly as much storage space as these cars.
snippet.textOriginal: Cargo space may be a deciding factor in purchasing a car. Advertised cargo capacity may be 68 ft³ for the Y and for the Model 3 it is 15 ft³. The actual storage capacity is measured to be much larger as shown in numerous reviews like https://youtu.be/5iHmM1MCQLs  The large under the trunk floor cavities and the front storage provide ample "covered" volume without a deck cover. Of course a blanket might be used as well to cover an oversize diamond... I am not aware of other vehicles with similar outside dimensions that provide nearly as much storage space as these cars.

I still sustain that Tesla is doing horribly designed cars with regards to internal utility.
